Hey <@U01UD8W2CLV>
There is no way to check the template name from the module by HubL but you can get the template path. To get the template path from the Design Manager, you can use the template path variable  {{ content.template_path }}.
Output: foldername/template_name.html
To get the template name from this, you have to use the modified code.
{{ content.template_path|replace("foldername/','')|replace('.html','') }}
Output: template_name

The actual code would be like this:
{% set tem = content.template_path|replace("foldername/','')|replace('.html','') %}
{% if tem == 'secondary' %}
// Do something here...
{% endif %}

I hope it will help you.

Thanks!
